channel.title: Czar Or Project Insanity
channel.description:
I want to make a server but I don't know which one to pick.
[center][b][i][u][size=18pt]Czar[/size][/u][/i][/b] Easier for me to code Easy to find classes Less-RuneScape like [/center]
[center][b][i][u][size=18pt]Project Insanity[/size][/u][/i][/b] RuneScape Like Skill-Cape Emotes Harder to code

item.title: Czar Or Project Insanity
item.dc:creator: @Java_Is_So_Cool Java Is So Cool
item.description:
@Java_Is_So_Cool wrote:

[quote=“I Vain I”]I wouldn’t recommend attempting Project Insanity, nor Czar.

If you want to learn effectively about the Java API, while using better code, and a server with better stability, then you need to go with Hyperion, RuneSource, or Rs377d.

Most of the other servers out at the moment are poorly programmed, and can’t handle more than twenty players, without a ten-gigabyte VPS.[/quote]
I dont hold anymore players then 40 without lagging haha, 8GBs of RAM and 1.05 ppload speed

Read full topic

item.title: Czar Or Project Insanity
item.dc:creator: @Sanskrit Sanskrit
item.description:
@Sanskrit wrote:

Pick Hyperion if you actually want to learn a little bit about the Java programming language and have the experience of writing your own class files from scratch.

Pick Project Insanity if you want to prance around yelling, “Hooway I have my own server!” like a child.

item.title: Czar Or Project Insanity
item.dc:creator: @Mendorphins Mendorphins
item.description:
@Mendorphins wrote:

gangsta tony:

Well I started with Czar Servers like 1-3 years ago, it was pretty good, then I moved to Delta Servers, Good but failed at making a webclient, then I moved to Bluurr, Now I don’t know what kind of server to make now. If I pick PI, would Project Rune be a good PI source or not?

Stick with what you feel comfortable with.

Make something unique, spend some time on it, and then if you decide to realease something it’s not some leeched server with a few things changed around.

You don’t want the attention, trust.

Read full topic
